2. Data Preprocessing
Preprocessed the dataset by encoding target labels and scaling features for robust model performance.
Handled missing values and ensured the data was ready for model training.
3. Model Development & Training
Implemented a Random Forest Classifier, which demonstrated excellent classification accuracy and interpretability.
Split the dataset into training (80%) and testing (20%) subsets to validate the modelâ€™s effectiveness.
4. Performance Evaluation
Achieved high accuracy, backed by precision, recall, F1-score, and a confusion matrix to assess performance.
Visualized predictions and performance metrics to better understand model reliability.
5. New Sample Predictions
Tested the model on new, unseen measurements of Iris flowers, accurately predicting their species with confidence.
